    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "But we're instantiating the helper with (https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch.js/blob/master/src/lib/InstantSearch.js#L103):\n\n``` js\n    let helper = algoliasearchHelper(\n      this.client,\n      this.searchParameters.index || this.indexName,\n      this.searchParameters\n    );\n```\n\nSo why would it solve the undefined index? With that code the underlying index name can never be `undefined`, isn't it?\n",
    "created_at": "2015-12-09T15:14:47Z",
    "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/pull/727#issuecomment-163286036",
    "id": 163286036,
