  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Well the url sync stores an initial configuration that is based [on the configuration of all the widgets](https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch.js/blob/develop/src/lib/InstantSearch.js#L99). It is the [last one to be called](https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch.js/blob/develop/src/lib/InstantSearch.js#L96) and this configuration will not contain the index name. \n\nThis is usually not a problem. But with Safari, the [popstate event](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/Events/popstate) is triggered before we render the url with the index name (from the line you showed). When the url is read the index name is empty and the initial configuration does not contain it either. And therefore when the popstate search is done, it leads to the error.\n",
    "created_at": "2015-12-09T15:28:05Z",
    "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/pull/727#issuecomment-163291699",
